<Class name="CM_CamControllerAgent" id="8f200162-8da6-438a-9ea6-a9f6b6b58e24">
    <superclass name="CM_Agent"/>
    <transient/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>
Typical Sequence (documented as part of MES1011 modifications)

startTask
   - deletes cam task  if exists  
   - create proxy cam task
		 - allocates processSeqNumber (unique within protocol) and dailySeqNumber (unique within day)
		 - sets status to 'extract status'
		 - create a peristent task history for unhSequenceNum if it doesn't exist

		 
extractAction
    - cam task status becomes 'extract status'
	- call CamProtoclDesc.buildFile
	       - finds transactions , creates a CM_CamFile
	            - If user-defined, runs JRW report and creates file in protocol directory, file content
		           also gets stored on cam task history.
		        - if not user-defined, builds email text and stores on cam task history
		   - trxSetupCamTaskHistory   - creates protocol output file , updates task history message count
		   - deletes the CM_CamFile

sendAction
    - if protocol on hold, exits
	- finds peristent task history for processSeqNumber
	- cam task status becomes 'send status' (2)
	- call CamProtocol.sendAction that 
	        - calls sendEmail (if email enabled) returns unique email id
			- calls sendFile (if file transfer enabled ) (new in MES1011)
	- updates task history message and stores unique email id


endTask
    - cam task status becomes 'complete status' (3)
	- trxEndTaskForProtocol
	      - cam protocol status becomes idle
		  - deletes cam task
	- creates activity history (CM_ActivityHistoryCams)
	
	
Other useful info
------------------
* If there are multiple days to be processed (has got behind or wound back), the CamTask runs for each date in the date range. 
  So multiple files may be produced. The standard Cam Files may skip numbers if there is a day wihtout transactions.
  The File Transfer numbers are always sequential cause they are only created if there is data
	</text>
    <DbClassMap file="cmtrans"/>
